While primarily used in correctional facilities for riot control, the OC Gun was introduced to the city's Metro division after a series of accidental deaths associated with other less-than-lethan weaponry. 

The weapon fires a low-velocity plastic-cased round filled with Oleoresin Capsicum, the active ingredient present in most pepper spray formulas. This gives the OC Gun the same effectiveness as OC spray at a much greater distance. 

This weapon can be used practically against targets without face protection or against individuals not under the influence of narcotics.
